00:12:41.920 --> 00:12:43.340
you pay more money.

00:12:43.450 --> 00:12:44.270
It's that simple.

00:12:47.300 --> 00:12:54.680
What people want is to have one network
with multiple flavors of computers.

00:12:56.460 --> 00:13:00.640
In the past, industry standards,
networking standards,

00:13:00.680 --> 00:13:04.070
were the way people wanted to
go down and make this happen.

00:13:05.180 --> 00:13:08.150
But if you look at how
the industry evolved,

00:13:08.150 --> 00:13:10.710
industry standards really didn't do it.

00:13:10.870 --> 00:13:14.890
It was too hard to make it
integrate and make everything work.

00:13:15.430 --> 00:13:22.180
Why people are excited about open
source is because open source is a way

00:13:22.210 --> 00:13:27.300
of doing a practical implementation
of a standards-based network.

00:13:27.380 --> 00:13:30.900
Because if one vendor uses
an implementation of TCP/IP,

00:13:30.900 --> 00:13:35.560
for instance,
that's identical to the other vendor,

00:13:35.610 --> 00:13:37.560
what are the likelihoods that
it's going to work together?

00:13:37.680 --> 00:13:38.460
It's very high.

00:13:38.570 --> 00:13:41.500
It's the same source code, right?

00:13:41.560 --> 00:13:43.680
So it's going to work.

00:13:44.870 --> 00:13:48.320
That's the power of open source,
is if everybody is using

00:13:48.620 --> 00:13:52.000
basically the same source to
do network interoperability,

00:13:52.000 --> 00:13:55.640
it's much easier for the
vendors to make it work.

00:13:57.180 --> 00:13:59.660
It's the same thing goes
with file compatibility.

00:13:59.750 --> 00:14:03.200
If we all can see what the source is,
that makes it possible for

00:14:03.320 --> 00:14:07.100
Apple to be compatible with Sun,
which can be compatible with IBM,

00:14:07.250 --> 00:14:10.940
which can be compatible with HP,
which is compatible with Linux,

00:14:10.940 --> 00:14:14.500
which is compatible with Solaris,
which is compatible with Mac OS X.

00:14:14.640 --> 00:14:19.710
So open source is a beautiful way,
it's a great mechanism to

00:14:19.860 --> 00:14:22.370
